Complaint for Declaratory and Injunctive Relief

evidence.text: Plaintiffs seek to declare these acts of the President unconstitutional, unlawful, and otherwise in excess of any constitutional or statutory authority; to hold unlawful and set aside the acts of agency defendants implementing his orders as unlawful and in violation of the Administrative Procedure Act; and to enjoin this unconstitutional reorganization of the federal government without legislative authority.
evidence.source_document: Complaint for Declaratory and Injunctive Relief

evidence.text: Plaintiffs filed this complaint to hold unlawful and stop the unconstitutional dismantling of the federal government by the President of the United States on a scale unprecedented in this country’s history and in clear excess of his authority.
evidence.source_document: Complaint for Declaratory and Injunctive Relief

evidence.text: Plaintiffs’ motion for a preliminary injunction, ECF No. 101 (PI Motion), and memorandum in support, ECF No. 101-1 (PI Brief), confirm that this sprawling lawsuit and Plaintiffs’ request for near government-wide relief does not belong in federal district court.
evidence.source_document: Defendants' Opposition to Plaintiffs' Motion for Preliminary Injunction
